The government intends to have all Chiefs and Assistant County Commissioners undergo paramilitary training to enhance their own safety and that of Wananchi under their areas of jurisdiction. This is according to interior CS Dr Fred Matiangi who says theÂ move will help to equip the administrative officers with the necessary skills to deal with terrorism and related incidents. Matiangi spoke in Nyeri town during the official opening of a three day training programme for deputy and assistant county commissioners drawn from the central Kenya region.